sentences: Mackenzie Ruth Scott (born January 23, 1991) is an American indie rock singer-songwriter who performs as Torres.
She began to perform in musicals, learned to play guitar, and started playing and singing hymns during church services and at a nursing home every week.
She graduated in December 2012.

In July 2012, while she was still a student, Scott recorded her debut album Torres over a five-day session at Tony Joe White's home studio in Franklin, Tennessee with engineer and producer Ryan McFadden.
Following the album's release on February 8, 2013, she played her debut show as Torres in Nashville at The Basement.
The album was digitally released on January 22, 2013 and received critical acclaim.
In the summer of 2013, she moved to Bushwick, Brooklyn.
In the summer of 2013, she moved to Bushwick, Brooklyn.
Scott appeared as a guest on Sharon Van Etten's 2014 album Are We There and released a single, "New Skin," through Weathervane Music in June 2014.
Scott appeared as a guest on Sharon Van Etten's 2014 album Are We There and released a single, "New Skin," through Weathervane Music in June 2014.
Sprinter (2015–2016)
Scott released her second album Sprinter on May 5, 2015 through Partisan Records.
She also opened for Garbage and Brandi Carlile, her early musical idol, in 2015, and joined Tegan and Sara for their November 2016 tour.

Three Futures (2017)
Scott's third album Three Futures was released on September 29, 2017.
Scott's third album Three Futures was released on September 29, 2017.
Three Futures takes inspiration from electro-pop, gothic industrial, and Krautrock.
Silver Tongue (2020)
Scott's fourth studio album Silver Tongue was released on January 31, 2020 via Merge Records.
"Dressing America" was selected as "Song of the Day" by Kevin Cole, the host of The Afternoon Show on KEXP-FM.
"Dressing America" was selected as "Song of the Day" by Kevin Cole, the host of The Afternoon Show on KEXP-FM.
Thirstier (2021)
Scott's fifth album, Thirstier, was released on July 30, 2021.
Her self-titled album TORRES received favorable reviews from Beats Per Minute, Pitchfork, and Metacritic.
Music website Pitchfork Media named Torres's debut single, "Honey," best new track, describing it as "an arena-rock moment happening on an empty stage
"Torres' third album Three Futures, which was released on September 29, 2017, has been met with positive reviews.
"Torres' third album Three Futures, which was released on September 29, 2017, has been met with positive reviews.

The AV Club also praises Three Futures describing it as "hazily fascinating, flowing naturally through its various peaks and valleys, and it succeeds in Scott's goal of being truly immersive listening," while rating the album an A-.

DIY also awarded Three Futures 4 out of 5 stars and noted Scott takes a step forward without forgetting what made her previous albums successful, by venturing into "previously little-trodden ground in sumptuous new ways."

DIY also awarded Three Futures 4 out of 5 stars and noted Scott takes a step forward without forgetting what made her previous albums successful, by venturing into "previously little-trodden ground in sumptuous new ways."
Scott is currently in a relationship with artist Jenna Gribbon, who designed the cover for her album Silver Tongue.
Scott announced their engagement in October, 2020.
On May 1, 2021, Scott came out as non-binary in a tweet.
